1
00:00:00,541 --> 00:00:03,791
Interviewer: How did you sleep in the room?

2
00:00:04,041 --> 00:00:07,166
Did you feel comfortable while sleeping?

3
00:00:07,583 --> 00:00:10,541
Honestly, there was no comfort

4
00:00:10,875 --> 00:00:13,375
First, fear, and second, planes all night

5
00:00:13,625 --> 00:00:17,291
And every minute, every moment you say, I’m dead

6
00:00:17,416 --> 00:00:19,958
Why? Because there is a chance we will be bombed

7
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,166
Because of their coming and going

8
00:00:22,291 --> 00:00:24,541
You say, We will be bombed, this place will be bombed

9
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:27,500
Especially when hearing the sound of airplanes

10
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,666
Terror takes hold in your heart

11
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:34,000
You sit and recite the <i>shahada</i>, and you brace yourself that you will die

12
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:38,208
Interviewer: How did you spend the time during the day?

13
00:00:38,416 --> 00:00:42,333
We spent it sitting and reading a verse, and so on

14
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,833
Interviewer: Were there Qurans inside the room?

15
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:49,500
Yes, there were pages and so on

16
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:53,875
But I still can’t read or write, I just held it for appearance

17
00:00:54,125 --> 00:00:57,250
Interviewer: The one who could read, did they force him to read or not?

18
00:00:57,333 --> 00:01:00,416
There were some who could read, with the Quran in hand, and they raised their voice

19
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,958
They told him to read so the others with him would listen

20
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:07,083
Interviewer: When you were inside the detention room

21
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:12,208
Was there a camera pointed at you so that everything you did was visible?

22
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,458
Were you visible to them inside the room?

23
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:17,375
I don’t know, maybe there was a camera

24
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:20,416
Maybe, but I don’t remember whether it was there or not

25
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:22,791
But I remember there was a camera

26
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,833
I remember, in the corner

27
00:01:25,916 --> 00:01:27,583
Interviewer: Did you think your rooms were monitored?

28
00:01:27,625 --> 00:01:29,458
Monitored, I remember, I swear to God

29
00:01:29,625 --> 00:01:31,958
But I’m not a hundred percent sure right now

30
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:35,458
Interviewer: While you were in that room?

31
00:01:35,541 --> 00:01:38,916
Was there a display screen there?

32
00:01:39,291 --> 00:01:43,458
Did ISIS show you its videos on that screen?

33
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:47,291
Execution videos, execution and amputation videos?

34
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:50,416
And battles, were they shown?

35
00:01:50,916 --> 00:01:53,750
In that room we didn’t have it

36
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:56,416
But after we left

37
00:01:57,041 --> 00:01:59,291
A young man who had been inside before asked me

38
00:01:59,416 --> 00:02:01,333
He said, They used to put it on a memory card

39
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:04,000
And show us those things

40
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:08,458
To keep fear in the prisoner’s heart

41
00:02:08,750 --> 00:02:09,750
Interviewer: In your room it wasn’t there?

42
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:11,041
No, in our room it wasn’t there

43
00:02:11,125 --> 00:02:15,166
But the same thing was in the halls

44
00:02:15,625 --> 00:02:16,833
It was in other places
